1
00:00:42,640 --> 00:00:44,631
Pardon the intrusion, gentlemen.

2
00:00:44,800 --> 00:00:47,268
William, good to see you.

3
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:49,553
What brings you up from Baltimore?

4
00:00:49,960 --> 00:00:51,871
The board at Columbia
asked for a consultation

5
00:00:51,960 --> 00:00:54,394
on how best to teach surgery
to their medical students.

6
00:00:54,480 --> 00:00:57,040
Aha. We're all the rage these days.

7
00:00:58,440 --> 00:01:01,796
Uh, William, let me introduce my apprentice,
Dr. John Thackery.

8
00:01:01,880 --> 00:01:04,189
Thack, this is Dr. William Halsted.

9
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:06,956
-Pleasure.
-Pleasure's all mine.

10
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:10,239
I had the good fortune
of working with your colleague

11
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:13,039
Dr. Osler in Philadelphia a few years back.

12
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:15,835
I know you're doing extraordinary things.

13
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:17,672
Well, you're in good hands yourself.

14
00:01:18,120 --> 00:01:21,795
J.M. was always a step ahead of me
in school, in sport,

15
00:01:21,880 --> 00:01:22,995
and with the women.

16
00:01:23,680 --> 00:01:26,911
Well, Dr. Thackery might best the both of us.

17
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:30,231
In short order, he's proven
himself indispensable to The Knick.

18
00:01:30,680 --> 00:01:33,877
High praise from someone
notoriously stingy with it.

19
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:36,434
After what you witness today,
you'll be praising this man

20
00:01:36,520 --> 00:01:39,193
in the hallways of your hospital
for years to come.

21
00:01:40,040 --> 00:01:43,191
Then let me take my seat
and let the games begin.

22
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:44,874
Good luck, gentlemen.

23
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:50,193
You didn't have to do that.

24
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:52,317
I meant every word of it.

25
00:01:52,520 --> 00:01:55,193
You're a comet in the sky, young Thack.

26
00:01:55,600 --> 00:01:56,828
Embrace it.

27
00:01:57,520 --> 00:01:59,988
I just feel that the surgery could very well fail.

28
00:02:00,080 --> 00:02:02,389
You've rehearsed it over and over
in the pathological lab.

29
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:03,993
It will succeed brilliantly.

30
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:05,872
We've got a full theater out there.

31
00:02:05,960 --> 00:02:09,555
Colleagues you've invited with the promise
of a great breakthrough today.

32
00:02:09,880 --> 00:02:12,872
A man whose life hangs in the balance.

33
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:16,238
It could be the biggest finding of my career,

34
00:02:16,720 --> 00:02:18,233
or an absolute disaster.

35
00:02:18,320 --> 00:02:19,673
You're just nervous.

36
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:21,631
I am. Aren't you?

37
00:02:21,880 --> 00:02:23,996
I won't be in a moment.

38
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:28,838
I wonder what Halsted would say
if he knew about this.

39
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:30,917
Who do you think told me about it?

40
00:02:32,720 --> 00:02:35,632
The appendix is a
rudimentary, functionless organ.

41
00:02:35,720 --> 00:02:40,555
A relic, really, and yet it still has the power
to fell a man in the prime of health

42
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:43,240
and has proven a difficult adversary.

43
00:02:44,640 --> 00:02:47,837
The patient on the table is 25. An attorney.

44
00:02:47,920 --> 00:02:50,229
No history of alcoholism or syphilis.

45
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:51,998
He was perfectly fit until yesterday,

46
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:54,355
when he was struck down
with acute abdominal pain.

47
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:57,637
Then Dr. Thackery quickly
deduced appendicitis.

48
00:02:58,240 --> 00:03:00,470
The pain has worsened, the fever risen.

49
00:03:00,720 --> 00:03:02,392
Vomiting began this morning.

50
00:03:02,480 --> 00:03:04,755
We could take the usual course
with therapeutics,

51
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:08,435
but we know these yield poor results
and most often death.

52
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:12,511
It is my belief that there is a way
to almost guarantee

53
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:18,197
full recovery in all appendicitis cases,
and that is the complete removal of the organ.

54
00:03:22,760 --> 00:03:23,954
They're ready.

55
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:25,952
Let's give 'em a show.

56
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:30,236
Dr. Thackery will make the first incision.

57
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:33,872
In countless trials,
Dr. Thackery has devised a way

58
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:37,032
in which to accurately determine
the location of the appendix,

59
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:41,796
thus eliminating the estimation
of where to make the initial incision.

60
00:03:43,480 --> 00:03:44,913
Dr. Thackery.

61
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:46,429
Surgical knife.

62
00:03:49,120 --> 00:03:51,475
By drawing a line
and divining the midway point

63
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:55,712
between the anterior-superior iliac spine
and the umbilicus,

64
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:58,633
parallel to the fibers of the external oblique,

65
00:03:59,120 --> 00:04:02,430
no matter what the size or sex of the patient,

66
00:04:06,040 --> 00:04:08,270
you will always find the appendix.

67
00:04:09,160 --> 00:04:10,388
And there it is.

68
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:14,070
The Thackery Point never misses.

69
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:19,589
Please, Johnny. Johnny, please.

70
00:04:19,680 --> 00:04:20,874
Please, Johnny.

71
