- Kill that nigger!

253
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:11,553
Thack.

254
00:15:11,720 --> 00:15:13,312
Thack!

255
00:15:13,640 --> 00:15:15,198
What are you doing? Help him!

256
00:15:20,880 --> 00:15:23,917
Stop it. Stop it. Leave him. Leave him!

257
00:15:26,840 --> 00:15:30,230
You're just standing there.
Help him, God damn it.

258
00:15:33,680 --> 00:15:36,194
Tell the nurses to lock
all the windows and doors.

259
00:15:36,280 --> 00:15:37,508
What happened?

260
00:15:37,720 --> 00:15:39,676
We need to get this man to the clinic.

261
00:15:41,480 --> 00:15:43,232
You need to stay out of sight.

262
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:07,872
Harry, I got one for you.

263
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:09,758
Been slashed to ribbons.

264
00:16:09,920 --> 00:16:13,037
Get me silk, two clamps,
and a Steinhart's needle.

265
00:16:17,160 --> 00:16:18,957
Can't see. Can you see anything?

266
00:16:19,080 --> 00:16:20,195
No.

267
00:16:23,720 --> 00:16:25,950
- Oh, watch yourself!
- Shit!

268
00:16:49,920 --> 00:16:51,911
No, stop.

269
00:16:52,240 --> 00:16:53,753
- You can't be in here.
- We need help.

270
00:16:53,840 --> 00:16:55,717
No, no, no. You need to get out.

271
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:57,472
- Hey, get them out of here.
- Back up.

272
00:16:57,560 --> 00:16:59,152
- No niggers allowed.
- You can't be here.

273
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:01,754
I said get out of here!
No niggers allowed!

274
00:17:01,840 --> 00:17:04,115
- Hey, hey!
- Hey, get off!

275
00:17:06,520 --> 00:17:08,351
Edwards!

276
00:17:11,160 --> 00:17:12,513
My apologies.

277
00:17:14,960 --> 00:17:16,712
We're gonna have to separate the room.

278
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:19,951
Let's get all the Negro patients
over to this side.

279
00:17:20,680 --> 00:17:22,113
You're letting them stay?

280
00:17:22,560 --> 00:17:25,028
-Thack, this isn't a Negro...
-Not the time, Everett.

281
00:17:25,280 --> 00:17:26,474
You got something to say
to his killer?

282
00:17:26,560 --> 00:17:28,039
I got something to say.

283
00:17:28,120 --> 00:17:29,155
Excuse me.

284
00:17:29,240 --> 00:17:30,958
What I got to say
you can't print in your paper.

285
00:17:31,040 --> 00:17:33,190
- Excuse me. Sorry. Sorry, ma'am.
- But I'll say it anyway.

286
00:17:33,320 --> 00:17:34,389
- Excuse me.
- What is it, lad?

287
00:17:34,480 --> 00:17:36,710
Them fucking darkies are...

288
00:17:42,120 --> 00:17:44,076
-Help me up, lad. Help me up.
-Whoa. Whoa.

289
00:17:46,160 --> 00:17:48,469
The one who killed our Phinny
is in the hospital.

290
00:17:50,840 --> 00:17:53,991
Them kids saw with their own eyes.
He snuck in the back.

291
00:17:54,160 --> 00:17:56,993
And they're treating
that murdering Quashee right now.

292
00:17:59,760 --> 00:18:00,909
Get the rope.

293
00:18:02,720 --> 00:18:05,632
The cotton-picker
that got Phinny's inside.

294
00:18:06,560 --> 00:18:07,879
Shit, they got ropes.

295
00:18:07,960 --> 00:18:08,995
-Really?
-Yeah.

296
00:18:09,080 --> 00:18:10,479
They get in, hit 'em with this.

297
00:18:11,080 --> 00:18:12,354
All right.

298
00:18:16,360 --> 00:18:18,749
I can't get away.
I'm having a bit of a situation here,

299
00:18:18,840 --> 00:18:21,593
but nothing to worry yourself about, dear.
All is well.

300
00:18:21,680 --> 00:18:22,715
It's fucking mayhem out there.

301
00:18:22,800 --> 00:18:24,836
They're gonna have the doors open
in about 10 seconds.

302
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:27,714
I just wouldn't come
south of 50th Street today.

303
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:28,994
All right?

304
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:30,679
I love you, too.

305
00:18:32,160 --> 00:18:35,436
Maybe the police should break up the crowd.

306
00:18:35,560 --> 00:18:37,835
The coppers are the ones
fucking spurring them on.

307
00:18:37,920 --> 00:18:39,399
God damn it!

308
00:18:41,240 --> 00:18:43,879
Heave! Heave!

309
00:18:52,560 --> 00:18:53,959
Shit.

310
00:19:15,720 --> 00:19:20,077
The mob is in the building.
They are destroying this hospital.

311
00:19:24,400 --> 00:19:27,949
Okay, listen, everybody.
We need to get the Negro patients out of here.

312
00:19:28,040 --> 00:19:29,075
You, help me.

313
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:34,111
We're gonna have to
treat them someplace else.

314
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:37,559
Let's take the south stairs
through the basement.

315
00:19:38,080 --> 00:19:39,877
Let's go. Quickly.

316
00:19:39,960 --> 00:19:41,712
There's a bunch of darkies in here!

317
00:19:52,240 --> 00:19:53,673
Hey!

318
00:20:05,760 --> 00:20:07,113
Come on!

319
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:12,119
Those are our fucking horses!

320
00:20:12,800 --> 00:20:14,313
Whose side are you on?

321
00:20:15,760 --> 00:20:16,988
This isn't a good idea.

322
00:20:17,080 --> 00:20:18,798
Drastic times.

323
00:20:20,960 --> 00:20:23,269
Where the hell are we going?

324
00:20:27,360 --> 00:20:29,635
What in God's name is this?

325
00:20:31,760 --> 00:20:33,113
Is this an operating room?

326
00:20:33,240 --> 00:20:35,629
An exam room, lavatory,
a postoperative ward,

327
00:20:35,720 --> 00:20:37,278
and whatever else I need it to be.

328
00:20:37,360 --> 00:20:38,429
You did this?

329
00:20:39,320 --> 00:20:40,594
You can't do this.

330
00:20:40,680 --> 00:20:42,238
I think he did.

331
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:44,235
And you knew?

332
00:20:44,320 --> 00:20:46,311
How else could I have helped him
as much as I did?

333
00:20:47,320 --> 00:20:49,117
It's only a matter of time till they find us here.

334
00:20:49,640 --> 00:20:50,868
Why? I never found it.

335
00:20:50,960 --> 00:20:52,598
They're obviously looking
harder than you did.

336
00:20:54,520 --> 00:20:55,714
Aren't you a laundress?

337
00:20:55,800 --> 00:20:57,870
Down here I am a surgical nurse.

338
00:20:58,600 --> 00:20:59,953
God help me.

339
00:21:00,760 --> 00:21:02,671
And did you steal all of this equipment?

340
00:21:03,920 --> 00:21:05,273
Most of it I bought.

341
00:21:05,360 --> 00:21:07,351
Other items I rescued and repaired.

342
00:21:07,480 --> 00:21:09,675
But not the obstetric equipment.

343
00:21:09,840 --> 00:21:11,034
I stole that.

344
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:13,797
You delivered babies down here?

345
00:21:13,880 --> 00:21:15,518
-Two.
-Algie.

346
00:21:18,680 --> 00:21:22,036
I want every Negro
out of this building right now.

347
00:21:22,120 --> 00:21:24,873
Mr. Barrow is right,
but not for the reasons he believes.

348
00:21:25,040 --> 00:21:29,318
Everyone here who can walk on their own
will have to find shelter elsewhere.

349
00:21:29,440 --> 00:21:31,032
But no one is safe out on the street.

350
00:21:31,160 --> 00:21:32,832
-Especially them.
-I'll take them.

351
00:21:33,360 --> 00:21:37,069
Our Lady of Sorrows has a friary
a few blocks down where they'll be safe.

352
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:39,236
Even hooligans won't riot in a church.

353
00:21:39,360 --> 00:21:40,509
They may leave, but I will not allow you...

354
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:42,238
Are you volunteering, then?

355
00:21:43,120 --> 00:21:45,554
-No.
-Then I'll thank you not to interfere.

356
00:21:46,440 --> 00:21:47,998
I'll have one of the other sisters
come with me.

357
00:21:48,080 --> 00:21:50,230
Thanks, Harry.
Everett, would you go with them?

358
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:52,589
Yes, Thack.

359
00:21:55,680 --> 00:21:57,910
Your recoveries, can they get on their feet?

360
00:21:58,520 --> 00:22:01,353
Certainly not well enough to
run through the streets in a riot.

361
00:22:01,440 --> 00:22:04,512
Then we'll have to transfer them
by ambulance to another facility.

362
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:06,272
Any ideas for a destination?

363
00:22:06,760 --> 00:22:09,069
The closest hospitals are
Presbyterian and Bellevue.

364
00:22:09,320 --> 00:22:10,309
Too far.

365
00:22:10,400 --> 00:22:11,913
The Jewish hospital will take them,

366
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:15,072
but that would mean crossing through
two Irish and one Italian ghetto.

367
00:22:15,160 --> 00:22:17,310
They belong in a Negro infirmary.

368
00:22:17,440 --> 00:22:20,159
There's one in Little Africa on Minetta.

369
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:24,912
How do we get outside
without being killed by that mob up there?

370
00:22:25,840 --> 00:22:27,558
Take the back stairs to the ambulance bay.

371
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:35,673
Where are the horses?

372
00:22:35,760 --> 00:22:37,432
Ask the fuckers who stole 'em.

373
00:22:40,040 --> 00:22:41,234
What do we do now?

374
00:22:41,320 --> 00:22:43,595
-We take them ourselves.
-On foot?

375
00:22:43,760 --> 00:22:47,719
Bertie, I need a surgeon to
stay here on call until we've returned.

376
00:22:47,800 --> 00:22:49,518
-Can you brave it?
-Of course.

377
00:22:49,880 --> 00:22:53,270
Dr. Edwards,
you can't be seen out there in plain sight.

378
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:55,908
I know, but I'm not leaving my patients.

379
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:58,639
We won't have enough of us
to transfer all the patients.

380
00:22:58,920 --> 00:23:00,433
Load the gurneys.

381
00:23:01,040 --> 00:23:02,439
I'll take the rest.

382
00:23:04,040 --> 00:23:05,393
How?

383
00:23:25,920 --> 00:23:27,114
How are you doing, Mr. Cleland?

384
00:23:27,200 --> 00:23:28,918
The bumps make it hurt.

385
00:23:29,320 --> 00:23:32,232
Hypodermic. Squibb's liquor of opium.

386
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:35,794
Arm or abdomen?

387
00:23:35,880 --> 00:23:37,279
Arm is fine.

388
00:23:37,960 --> 00:23:39,313
You want me to stop moving?

389
00:23:40,200 --> 00:23:41,838
Not unless you need to.

390
00:23:46,640 --> 00:23:48,551
Everyone stay under your wraps.

391
00:23:52,920 --> 00:23:54,717
And where are you all going?

392
00:23:55,720 --> 00:23:57,119
We're heading downtown.

393
00:23:57,240 --> 00:23:59,151
I meant more specific like.

394
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:01,274
What you got under there?

395
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:04,034
Just let us pass
and you won't have any trouble.

396
00:24:04,720 --> 00:24:06,756
You'll have trouble if I say you do.

397
00:24:06,880 --> 00:24:08,438
We're headed to the city morgue.

398
00:24:08,520 --> 00:24:10,875
- What for?
- Leprosy outbreak.

399
00:24:11,240 --> 00:24:13,231
Can't keep them at The Knick.
Need to burn the bodies down there

400
00:24:13,320 --> 00:24:15,356
before anyone else gets it.

401
00:24:15,520 --> 00:24:18,114
You can look, but about a week from now,
you're gonna be down on your knees

402
00:24:18,200 --> 00:24:20,714
trying to find
where your testicles rolled off to.

403
00:24:31,840 --> 00:24:34,274
Away! Back away, I tell you!

404
00:24:34,360 --> 00:24:35,918
You'll all be damned to hell

405
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:37,752
if you touch one hair
on these people's heads!

406
00:24:37,840 --> 00:24:39,193
Keep walking.

407
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:42,272
You'll all face the fires of hell
if I have anything to say about it.

408
00:24:42,360 --> 00:24:43,588
And you know I do.

409
00:24:43,680 --> 00:24:46,114
One of them could be
the fella that killed Phinny Sears!

410
00:24:46,200 --> 00:24:48,555
Hump off! You didn't even know the man.

411
00:25:00,080 --> 00:25:01,832
I think they've finally given up.

412
00:25:02,840 --> 00:25:04,478
I suppose they have.

413
00:25:05,280 --> 00:25:08,078
Probably off to go destroy
someone else's place.

414
00:25:08,440 --> 00:25:09,634
Wherever that may be.

415
00:25:09,720 --> 00:25:11,915
As long as it isn't here, I don't give a damn.

416
00:25:13,280 --> 00:25:15,475
Let's finish cleaning up this glass,

417
00:25:15,600 --> 00:25:18,512
and we need inventories on
all medicines and equipment.

418
00:25:18,920 --> 00:25:20,273
And patients.

419
00:25:20,600 --> 00:25:22,556
I want all patients accounted for.

420
00:25:24,320 --> 00:25:25,958
Don't put any weight on it.

421
00:25:26,040 --> 00:25:28,508
Just go home and get some rest.

422
00:25:28,760 --> 00:25:31,558
Fuck home. I'm going uptown.

423
00:25:31,800 --> 00:25:33,870
They got all the whores
turned out in the street.

424
00:25:34,120 --> 00:25:35,758
Fellas are running trains on them.

425
00:25:36,040 --> 00:25:37,837
Cops are too busy to do anything about it.

426
00:25:45,360 --> 00:25:49,239
Nobody leaves
until this place is back the way it was.

427
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:33,628
Who's in charge here?

428
00:26:33,720 --> 00:26:35,597
Dr. Williams. Over there.

429
00:26:41,520 --> 00:26:42,999
Dr. Williams?

430
00:26:43,680 --> 00:26:46,319
I'm Dr. John Thackery,
Chief of Surgery over at The Knick.

431
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:49,198
This is my assistant chief,
Dr. Algernon Edwards.

432
00:26:49,600 --> 00:26:51,511
-Algie.
-Moses Williams.

433
00:26:51,600 --> 00:26:53,830
-You know each other?
-We were at Harvard together.

434
00:26:53,920 --> 00:26:56,514
Moses was the one in his year
and I was the one in mine.

435
00:26:57,440 --> 00:26:59,874
-I'd shake hands, but...
-Of course.

436
00:27:00,080 --> 00:27:02,878
We know you're overrun here,
but we brought you seven more.

437
00:27:02,960 --> 00:27:04,678
It was too dangerous
to keep them at The Knick.

438
00:27:04,760 --> 00:27:07,035
We'll help out in any way we can.

439
00:27:07,520 --> 00:27:09,954
Then pick a patient, get started.

440
00:27:10,440 --> 00:27:12,795
You're welcome to any of our supplies.

441
00:27:13,120 --> 00:27:15,475
Thank you. We're out of just about everything.

442
00:27:15,560 --> 00:27:19,269
Thread, carbolic, clean bandages,
alum, cocaine.

443
00:27:21,360 --> 00:27:22,918
We'll make do.

444
00:27:28,840 --> 00:27:30,592
You see anything that way?

445
00:27:42,840 --> 00:27:44,592
Keep moving, buddy. It's closed.

446
00:27:44,840 --> 00:27:46,398
But, Officer, I'm family.

447
00:27:46,640 --> 00:27:48,392
Of a worker in a whore shop?

448
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:50,956
For the love of Christ,
the whole town's going crazy

449
00:27:51,040 --> 00:27:52,837
and you want to get your fucking log dunked?

450
00:27:52,960 --> 00:27:55,474
No one's going in the establishment
till this fracas is over.

451
00:27:55,560 --> 00:27:58,472
I understand, but this is urgent.

452
00:27:59,200 --> 00:28:02,829
Do I look like one of these hooligans
tearing the streets apart?

453
00:28:03,080 --> 00:28:05,594
I don't give a good goddamn
if you're the second coming.

454
00:28:05,680 --> 00:28:07,796
You're not going in.
Now take it on the arches.

455
00:28:08,080 --> 00:28:10,230
-Excuse me.
-Go on, get! Get!

456
00:28:10,320 --> 00:28:12,754
-All right! God damn it!
-Get out!

457
00:28:18,360 --> 00:28:19,873
Hurry up! They're coming here!

458
00:28:27,920 --> 00:28:29,399
Junia.

459
00:28:29,800 --> 00:28:31,597
I just wanted to make sure you were...

460
00:28:33,960 --> 00:28:37,111
I'm fine, Hermie, but you need to go.

461
00:28:38,200 --> 00:28:40,316
I'm nearly done if you're next.

462
00:28:57,680 --> 00:28:59,398
You can put it down.

463
00:29:07,680 --> 00:29:09,113
You need a break?

464
00:29:09,800 --> 00:29:12,075
I can have someone else
step in to help me finish.

465
00:29:12,160 --> 00:29:13,388
No, I'm fine.

466
00:29:13,880 --> 00:29:15,472
And there are so many more.

467
00:29:17,440 --> 00:29:18,998
Towel.

468
00:29:22,200 --> 00:29:23,679
For you.

469
00:29:28,480 --> 00:29:29,959
Jamison.

470
00:29:30,640 --> 00:29:32,756
-Who is Jamison?
-That's me. I am.

471
00:29:40,240 --> 00:29:41,389
What do we have?

472
00:29:41,480 --> 00:29:43,550
Gashed upper thigh and buttocks.

473
00:29:46,880 --> 00:29:48,871
Dr. Williams, have a look at this.

474
00:29:51,920 --> 00:29:53,273
He's cut through to the bone.

475
00:29:53,400 --> 00:29:55,038
We'll have to sew it up in layers.

476
00:29:55,120 --> 00:29:57,031
We have no more anesthetic.

477
00:29:57,200 --> 00:29:59,031
No morphine, no cocaine.

478
00:29:59,600 --> 00:30:01,113
We'll just have to hold him down.

479
00:30:01,200 --> 00:30:04,192
- He's gonna thrash.
- We will make do.

480
00:30:08,360 --> 00:30:09,679
Edwards.

481
00:30:17,240 --> 00:30:19,549
You don't have to stay with me
if this is too offensive for you.

482
00:30:19,640 --> 00:30:21,073
I've seen a buttock before.

483
00:30:21,280 --> 00:30:23,077
-A black one?
-Yes, yours.

484
00:30:23,360 --> 00:30:24,873
When we'd play in the garden
with the water pails

485
00:30:24,960 --> 00:30:27,155
and you'd run around without pants.

486
00:30:27,240 --> 00:30:29,151
-We were three.
-And he saw mine.

487
00:30:29,240 --> 00:30:30,798
For God's sake, Neely.

488
00:30:47,880 --> 00:30:48,915
Suction.

489
00:30:55,680 --> 00:30:57,079
That's enough.

490
00:30:58,960 --> 00:31:00,439
What's next?

491
00:31:01,480 --> 00:31:03,710
"Pass the needles through the intestinal wall

492
00:31:03,840 --> 00:31:07,276
"one half-inch below
and, drawing the threads,

493
00:31:07,360 --> 00:31:11,638
"invaginate the end of the upper portion
into the lower through the slit."

494
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:14,719
Okay, but this is intraperitoneal.
So what do I do then?

495
00:31:16,400 --> 00:31:17,799
I don't know.

496
00:31:18,200 --> 00:31:20,270
Okay, well, show me the photograph.

497
00:31:22,800 --> 00:31:24,119
So I can see it.

498
00:31:29,120 --> 00:31:30,314
Got it.

499
00:31:42,920 --> 00:31:44,114
Sorry.

500
00:31:47,080 --> 00:31:48,195
Who's next?

501
00:31:48,320 --> 00:31:50,151
This is the last patient.

502
00:31:54,280 --> 00:31:57,397
Then it looks as though
our work here is done.

503
00:31:59,200 --> 00:32:01,998
It would be nice to catch up
in quieter circumstances.

504
00:32:02,640 --> 00:32:05,837
Find out how you landed at The Knick
with the great John Thackery.

505
00:32:05,960 --> 00:32:07,359
I'd like that.

506
00:32:07,840 --> 00:32:09,159
Take care, Moses.

507
00:32:12,040 --> 00:32:13,837
Thank you.

508
00:32:15,680 --> 00:32:18,035
The rain seems to have calmed things a bit.

509
00:32:18,280 --> 00:32:22,353
It may seem quiet,
but we have no idea how safe the streets are.

510
00:32:22,520 --> 00:32:24,511
Well, we can load the gurneys
in the ambulance,

511
00:32:24,600 --> 00:32:26,272
but I ain't got the strength
to pull 'em back alone.

512
00:32:26,360 --> 00:32:28,032
So you got to keep pushing.

513
00:32:28,520 --> 00:32:30,511
-I'll help you.
-I'll come, too.

514
00:32:30,920 --> 00:32:33,115
I want to check on the condition of things.

515
00:32:33,200 --> 00:32:35,509
I'm sure my office is a shambles.

516
00:32:35,920 --> 00:32:40,118
Then I'll see Nurse Elkins gets home safely
and I'll meet you there.

517
00:32:41,200 --> 00:32:42,679
What about my bike?

518
00:32:44,480 --> 00:32:46,675
Well, if it hasn't
already become a victim of the riot,

519
00:32:46,760 --> 00:32:48,512
it certainly won't at this point.

520
00:32:48,840 --> 00:32:50,717
You can get it in the morning.

521
00:32:56,720 --> 00:32:57,914
All right.

522
00:33:57,320 --> 00:33:58,719
Unbelievable.

523
00:34:13,320 --> 00:34:15,550
I thought for certain
all this would be destroyed.

524
00:34:16,120 --> 00:34:17,792
They didn't even come down here.

525
00:34:18,880 --> 00:34:22,475
I guess I pushed you across town
under a gurney for nothing.

526
00:34:23,160 --> 00:34:25,310
Not for nothing.

527
00:34:28,320 --> 00:34:29,799
What sex?

528
00:34:31,600 --> 00:34:32,828
What?

529
00:34:32,960 --> 00:34:34,916
The babies you delivered.

530
00:34:35,640 --> 00:34:37,073
Oh.

531
00:34:37,840 --> 00:34:40,752
Um, two girls.

532
00:34:43,920 --> 00:34:46,309
You've become someone I didn't expect.

533
00:34:47,480 --> 00:34:50,278
What, a sneak with a scalpel,

534
00:34:50,720 --> 00:34:52,756
plying his trade in dark corners?

535
00:34:52,840 --> 00:34:55,513
No, though that was a surprise.

536
00:34:58,720 --> 00:35:00,676
Then what have I become?

537
00:35:02,600 --> 00:35:04,955
You did something remarkable here.

538
00:35:06,880 --> 00:35:10,156
And to watch you today...

539
00:35:14,040 --> 00:35:17,828
I suppose I still thought of you
as that little boy I grew up with.

540
00:35:20,720 --> 00:35:23,314
The one without the pants?

541
00:35:23,400 --> 00:35:25,152
The very same one.

542
00:35:30,240 --> 00:35:32,310
I was terrified for you today.

543
00:35:33,440 --> 00:35:35,590
The whole city wanting to hurt you.

544
00:35:36,040 --> 00:35:38,508
And with only you to protect me.

545
00:35:39,400 --> 00:35:40,719
I would have.

546
00:35:42,400 --> 00:35:44,197
I have no doubt.

547
00:36:21,040 --> 00:36:24,237
I doubt I'm allowed much further.

548
00:36:25,160 --> 00:36:26,275
It's all right.

549
00:36:26,440 --> 00:36:29,716
I'm sure the housemother is still asleep
and she's practically deaf.

550
00:36:40,600 --> 00:36:43,068
I guess it was a good thing
things were happening so fast,

551
00:36:43,160 --> 00:36:44,593
'cause I didn't have any time to think.

552
00:36:44,720 --> 00:36:46,676
Well, you did brilliantly.

553
00:36:47,440 --> 00:36:49,237
Okay, good night, Nurse Elkins.

554
00:36:49,800 --> 00:36:51,552
Really well done today.

555
00:36:52,360 --> 00:36:54,476
My roommate's already gone to work.

556
00:36:55,640 --> 00:36:57,278
You can come in if you like.

557
00:37:53,360 --> 00:37:55,157
I need help taking this off.

558
00:38:11,160 --> 00:38:12,957
Will it hurt?

559
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:21,877
I can make it painless

560
00:38:23,200 --> 00:38:24,838
and perfect.

561
00:40:19,680 --> 00:40:21,352
Hi.

562
00:40:24,200 --> 00:40:25,553
What?

563
00:40:26,040 --> 00:40:27,359
What?

564
00:40:28,520 --> 00:40:30,397
What?

